OL,6,FIn papers published ahead of
OL,7,FFebruary's Court of Session hearing,
OL,8,Fthe Scottish Government argued that a
OL,9,F"blanket rule" stating that a
OL,10,F"transgender prisoner can only be
OL,11,Fplaced in the prison according to
OL,12,Ftheir biological sex would violate the
OL,13,Frights of some prisoners".
OL,15,FIt added that placing prisoners in a
OL,16,Fprison for those of the opposite
OL,17,Fbiological sex may be required to
OL,18,Fprevent a violation of the Human
OL,19,FRights Act.
