OL,6,FIt stated that the types of prisoner
OL,7,Fwho have been placed in a prison for
OL,8,Fthe sex opposite to that which they
OL,9,Fwere born into included inmates with a
OL,10,Fgender recognition certificate, those
OL,11,Fwho have lived in their acquired
OL,12,Fgender "for decades" and a "transman
OL,13,Fof masculine appearance".
OL,15,FHowever offenders are not placed in a
OL,16,Fprison "solely on the basis of those
OL,17,Fpersonal attributes", the paper said,
OL,18,Fadding that an "individualised
OL,19,Fassessment" is carried out in line
OL,20,Fwith prisons guidance.
